wikilambda-editor-name-aliases-descripti: Aliases are alternatives for the function. For example, if the function is called ‚ÄúAdd‚Äù, and it adds two numbers together, possible aliases might be ‚ÄúAddition‚Äù, ‚ÄúSum‚Äù, or ‚ÄúFindSum‚Äù.

wikilambda-editor-input-description: Inputs are the values that are passed into the function. For example, if the function is called ‚ÄúAdd‚Äù, and it adds two numbers together, the inputs might be ‚Äúx‚Äù and ‚Äúy‚Äù.
wikilambda-editor-output-subtitle: What will come out of the function?
wikilambda-editor-output-description: The output of a function is the result of the function. For example, the output of the function ‚ÄúAdd‚Äù is the sum of the two inputs.

wikilambda-function-about-summary: This function turns an English singular word into its plural form, but English is a weird language and it might get some rarely used words incorrect. Give it a try!
wikilambda-function-details-summary: Anyone can propose a new implementation or test. Proposed code is reviewed by the Wikifunctions community before it becomes an available implementation or verified test.
wikilambda-function-details-summary-lear: Learn more about the review process.
wikilambda-function-viewer-details-sideb: Anyone can edit labels, but the input/output type and count can only be edited by users with special permissions.
